## 4. Preparing Test Cases

The table below documents all ten test cases for this component. "Normal" means a straightforward happy path; "Edge" means a boundary or limit condition; "Invalid" means deliberately absent or nonsensical input.

| TestID | Scenario | Input | Expected Result | Test Type |
|--------|----------|-------|-----------------|-----------|
| TC01 | Browse all listings | GET /browse/ with no params | HTTP 200; all available (non-deleted) items appear in the result set | Normal |
| TC02 | Search by keyword | GET /browse/?q=phone | HTTP 200; only items containing "phone" in title or description are returned | Normal |
| TC03 | Search with no results | GET /browse/?q=xyzabc123 | HTTP 200; result set is empty (count = 0, object_list length = 0) | Invalid |
| TC04 | Filter by category | GET /browse/?category=\<pk\> | HTTP 200; only items belonging to that category are returned | Normal |
| TC05 | Filter by price range | GET /browse/?min_price=0&max_price=500 | HTTP 200; only items priced ≤ 500 are returned; items above 500 are excluded | Edge |
| TC06 | Filter by condition | GET /browse/?condition=new | HTTP 200; only items with condition='new' are returned | Normal |
| TC07 | Sort by price low to high | GET /browse/?sort=price_asc | HTTP 200; items in page_obj are ordered by ascending itemPrice | Normal |
| TC08 | Combine search + filter | GET /browse/?q=phone&category=\<pk\> | HTTP 200; only items matching both the keyword and the category appear | Normal |
| TC09 | Anonymous access | GET /browse/ by a logged-out client | HTTP 200 (no redirect); the browse page is public | Edge |
| TC10 | Pagination boundary | 15 items created; GET /browse/?page=1 then ?page=2 | Page 1 returns 12 items; page 2 returns the remaining 3; total count = 15 | Edge |

